  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dca \u0d86\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dba\u0d9a \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dab \u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dbd\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A low-cost test kit to identify Covid-infected patients",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Antigen and PCR to identify Covid-infected patients. A team including a senior lecturer at the University of Peradeniya has created a test kit that can be used as an intermediate test method.",
        "Peradeniya University Vice Chancellor Professor M.D. This design was introduced to the Minister of Health Dr. Keheliya Rambukwella by a group including Mr. Kalpawansa and senior lecturer Mr. Ruchika Fernando who designed the device. This enables the identification of infected people quickly and at low cost.",
        "According to its designer, the related test can be done with an amount of 1500 rupees. Currently, it has received approval from the National Drug Regulatory Authority's Technical Committee and is awaiting registration. Meanwhile, this particular test set \"RT LAMP (Reverse Transcription Loop Mediated Isothermal Amplification)\" has applied for the national and international patent.",
        "The Minister of Health said that according to the \"vision of prosperity\", the maximum support that can be provided for local products is given, and especially in the face of the Covid disaster, it is extremely important that such products are created by Sri Lankan designers."
      ],
